Attributes.Label: About Me
Attributes.Value: Hi! HI HI HI! Did ya hear me? Oh, good. I'm Mookie, or Blossom, or whatever you'd like! I'm a talkative and outgoing full grown lady of nearly 7 years.  I'm pretty set in my ways but still optimistic for a home and family that would suit me! I really don't like other dogs and it's unlikely that I'll like cats any better. Respectful and savvy children would probably be alright but I can be a little off-putting sometimes so no-one too timid or faint of heart, kay? I'm ready for walks, naps, adventures abound! Let's get a move on! there is so much to see and do! So many beds left un-napped in! Come meet me today!

Attributes.Label: About Me
Attributes.Value: Hello! I'm Fonora! I'm an adorable 4 year old girl who is so tired of being lonely! I have many positive qualities that seem to be going overlooked. I am petite and energetic. I love to go on walks! The world might be a big scary place but I'm not gonna let it keep me down! I wanna bounce right alongside you and face all our problems together! Unless it's dogs. I don't want to face any dogs. I don't like them. I've never met a cat, not sure if I want to. If you're not a dog I'm sure we'll get along great. I really enjoy giving hugs! You'll have to see it to believe it! We'll be an unstoppable duo but you have to come meet me to get that duo started! See you soon!

Attributes.Label: About Me
Attributes.Value: Misty is an estimated 12 year old pointer / beagle mix who came to us after her owners could no longer care for her. Her previous owners described Misty as very loveable and said she even knows a few commands. Misty was reported to be good with older children and cats, but does not do well with smaller dogs or young children. Misty had an incident several years ago when she bit a small child who was picking food off the floor. We are trying to get Misty out to a rescue in a foster based setting, who has the resources to train and work with her in finding her forever home, preferably without children. During examination, Misty was found to have moderate dental disease and two masses that seem most likely to be lipomas.

Attributes.Label: About Me
Attributes.Value: Johnson!!! That's me! I am the cutest dog you have ever laid eyes on (or so I'd like to think) and I am ready to be welcomed into your home so I can start my new life. I'm still a young pup, so I have lots of energy and need to go to a home where I can get daily exercise to burn that energy off. We could go for walk, or hikes, or play fetch, I mean the possibilities are just endless! We could be great pals and do almost everything together! Now that summer is here, the sunny days are perfect for outside adventures, so come in and adopt me so we can start our life together!

Attributes.Label: About Me
Attributes.Value: Grady is an estimated 2 year old Cane Corso who came to us as an owner surrender. Her previous owner described Grady as affectionate, but said that she had a little too much energy for their household. Grady is reported to get along well with children and cats, but is selective of dogs and wary of strangers.  While Grady was well behaved for her behavior evaluation, she definitely presents very timid around people she does not know. Due to her size and temperament, rescue placement is preferred in order to assure Grady finds her forever home. This 84lb girl has been spayed, microchipped, fully vaccinated, tested negative for heartworms and has no known medical concerns.

Attributes.Label: About Me
Attributes.Value: Core is an estimated 2 year old Rottweiler that came to us as a stray. This handsome guy was very selective of people upon intake, so he has been under increased behavior modification. While Core has made improvements with us, rescue placement is preferred for this handsome boy. Core is seeing a rescue who has the resources to continue his training, and find him a home that will bring out the best in him!

Attributes.Label: About Me
Attributes.Value: Fatz is 4 year old Bulldog/Boxer mix, approximately 50lbs, who came to us as an owner surrender. This handsome guy is extremely reactive to other dogs in both a home environment and a shelter setting, and attacked a small dog in his previous home. His previous owner described Fatz as playful and good with kids, but had not been exposed to cats. We have seen no signs of aggression to humans during socialization or routine veterinary care, but he is in need of a home where he can be the only dog. Fatz is neutered, microchipped, fully vaccinated, tested negative for heartworms and has no known medical concerns.
